92 /* DesignId : MMWL_DesignId_073 */
93 /* Requirements : AUTORADAR_REQ-768 */
94 rlReturnVal_t rlRfDigMonEnableConfig(rlUInt8_t deviceMap, rlMonDigEnables_t* data)
95 {
96  rlReturnVal_t retVal;
97 
98  /* check if deviceIndex is out of defined value */
99  if ((rlDriverIsDeviceMapValid(deviceMap) != RL_RET_CODE_OK) || (RL_NULL_PTR == data))
100  {
101  /* set return error code */
102  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
103  }
104  else
105  {
106  /* Package the command with given data and send it to device */
107  retVal = rlDriverExecuteSetApi(deviceMap, RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG,
108  RL_RF_DIG_MON_EN_SB, (rlUInt8_t*)data,
109  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlMonDigEnables_t));
110  }
111  return retVal;
112 }

383 /* DesignId : MMWL_DesignId_080 */
384 /* Requirements : AUTORADAR_REQ-861 */
385 rlReturnVal_t rlRfTxPowrMonConfig(rlUInt8_t deviceMap, rlAllTxPowMonConf_t *data)
386 {
387  rlReturnVal_t retVal;
388  /* Initialize Command and Response Sub Blocks */
389  rlDriverMsg_t inMsg;
390  rlDriverMsg_t outMsg = {0};
391  rlUInt16_t numSbc = 0U;
392 
393  /* Initialize Command and Response Sub Blocks */
394  rlPayloadSb_t inPayloadSb[RL_MAX_SB_IN_MSG] = {0};
395 
396  RL_LOGV_ARG0("rlRfTxPowrMonConfig starts...\n");
397 
398  /* Construct command packet */
399  rlDriverConstructInMsg(RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG, &inMsg, &inPayloadSb[0U]);
400 
401  /* check if deviceIndex is out of defined value */
402  if ((rlDriverIsDeviceMapValid(deviceMap) != RL_RET_CODE_OK) || \
403  (RL_NULL_PTR == data))
404  {
405  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
406  RL_LOGE_ARG0("rlRfTxPowrMonConfig, Invalid input \n");
407  }
408  else
409  {
410  /* check for NULL pointer */
411  if ((RL_NULL_PTR != data->tx0PowrMonCfg))
412  {
413  /* Fill in-message Payload */
414  rlDriverFillPayload(RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG,
415  RL_RF_TX0_POW_MON_CONF_SB,
416  &inPayloadSb[numSbc],
417  (rlUInt8_t* )data->tx0PowrMonCfg,
418  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlTxPowMonConf_t));
419  numSbc++;
420  }
421  /* check for NULL pointer */
422  if ((RL_NULL_PTR != data->tx1PowrMonCfg))
423  {
424  /* Fill in-message Payload */
425  rlDriverFillPayload(RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG,
426  RL_RF_TX1_POW_MON_CONF_SB,
427  &inPayloadSb[numSbc],
428  (rlUInt8_t* )data->tx1PowrMonCfg,
429  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlTxPowMonConf_t));
430  numSbc++;
431  }
432  /* check for NULL pointer */
433  if ((RL_NULL_PTR != data->tx2PowrMonCfg))
434  {
435  /* Fill in-message Payload */
436  rlDriverFillPayload(RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG,
437  RL_RF_TX2_POW_MON_CONF_SB,
438  &inPayloadSb[numSbc],
439  (rlUInt8_t* )data->tx2PowrMonCfg,
440  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlTxPowMonConf_t));
441  numSbc++;
442  }
443 
444  if (numSbc > 0U)
445  {
446  /* setting num of sub-block to inMsg */
447  inMsg.opcode.nsbc = numSbc;
448 
449  /* Send Command to mmWave Radar Device */
450  retVal = rlDriverCmdInvoke(deviceMap, inMsg, &outMsg);
451  }
452  else
453  {
454  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
455  RL_LOGE_ARG0("sub block is NULL\n");
456  }
457  }
458 
459  return retVal;
460 }

871  if ((RL_NULL_PTR != data->tx2IntAnaSgnlMonCfg))
872  {
873  /* Fill in-message Payload */
874  rlDriverFillPayload(RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG,
875  RL_RF_TX2_INT_ANA_SIGNALS_MON_CONF_SB,
876  &inPayloadSb[numSbc],
877  (rlUInt8_t* )data->tx2IntAnaSgnlMonCfg,
878  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlTxIntAnaSignalsMonConf_t));
879  numSbc++;
880  }
881 
882  if (numSbc > 0U)
883  {
884  /* setting num of sub-block to inMsg */
885  inMsg.opcode.nsbc = numSbc;
886 
887  /* Send Command to mmWave Radar Device */
888  retVal = rlDriverCmdInvoke(deviceMap, inMsg, &outMsg);
889  }
890  else
891  {
892  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
893  RL_LOGE_ARG0("sub block is NULL\n");
894  }
895  }
896 
897  return retVal;
898 }
